課程概述：如何學好物理化學.mp4





導論：物理化學各領域的關係.mp4





第一章 Systems, States, and Processes1-1-1-2 一些基本的單位定義及觀念.mp4





1-3 對氣體的描述：理想氣體及真實氣體.mp4





1-4 PVT surface及臨界點.mp4





1-5 熱力學所需之數學.mp4





第二章 The Equilibrium Macroscopic States of Gases and Liquids2-1-2-2 熱力學的簡單發展史及功與熱.mp4





2-3 Internal Energy：The First Law of Thermodynamics2-4 Calculation of Amounts of Heat and Energy Changes2-5 Enthalpy.mp4





2-5 Enthalpy2-6 Application to Ideal Gas2-7 Application to Non-Ideal Gas.mp4





2-8 Calculation of Enthalpy Changes of Process without Chemical Reaction.mp4





第三章 Second and Third Laws of Thermodynamics: Entropy3-1 The Second Law of Thermodynamics and the Carnot Engine.mp4





3-2 The Mathematical Statement of the Second Law: Entropy.mp4





3-3 The Calculation of Entropy Changes3-4 Statistical Entropy3-5 Third Law of Thermodynamics and Absolute Entropies.mp4





第四章 The Second and Third Laws of Thermodynamics：Entropy4.1-4.2 G(Gibbs)和A(Helmholtz)自由能及動力學的基礎公式.mp4





4-4 Gibbs Energy Calculation.mp4





4-5 Multicomponent System4-6 Eulers Theorem and the Gibbs-Duhem Relation.mp4





第五章 The Thermodynamics of Real Systems5-1 The Fundamental Fact of Phase Equilibrium5-2 The Gibbs Phase Rule5-3 Phase equilibrium in 1-component systems5-4 The Gibbs Energy and Phase Transitions.mp4





5-4 The Gibbs Energy and Phase Transitions5-5 Surface in One-Component System.mp4





第六章 The Thermodynamics of Solutions 6-1 Ideal Solutions.mp4





6-2 Henrys Law and Dilute Nonelectrolyte Solution6-3 Activity and activity coefficients.mp4





6-5 Thermodynamic Functions of Nonideal Solutions6-6 Phase Diagrams of Non-ideal mixtures6-7 Colligative (tied together) Properties(依數性質).mp4





第七章 Chemical Equilibrium 7-1 ΔG and the Equilibrium Constant7-2 Reactions Involving Gases and Pure Solids or Liquids7-3 Chemical Equilibrium in Solutions.mp4





7-4 Debye-Hückel Theory7-5 Buffer Solutions7-6 Temp. Dependence7-7 Biological Systems.mp4





第八章 The Thermodynamics of Electrochemical Systems8-1 The Chemical Potential and the Electric Potential8-2 Electrochemical Cells8-3 Half-cell Potentials and Cell Potentials.mp4





8-4 Determination of a± and g ± of Electrolytes8-5 Determination of pH8-6 Thermodynamic for Electrochemistry8-6 Ion Mobility and Transference Number (補充).mp4





